Drag & drop issues/cards in GreenHopper taskboard is broken (the process keeps spinning) using IE8

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-6309].
  {panel}

- Sub tasks not included by the board's filter should still displayed on the board if the parent is displayed.

This documentation need to clarify which Planning Board and Task Board the Flag is applies:
{quote}
This field is of type 'Multi Checkboxes' and is available to all issue types. (See also Setting up a Flagging Field — this applies only to the Planning Board and Task Board.)
{quote}

https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/GreenHopper+JIRA+Configuration

Coming from a dedicated customer:

{quote}
It is quite in efficient and time consuming to add issues to sprints in progress: You have to open the rapid board, go to plan mode, search up the issue, drag and drop from backlog to sprint. With an operation available through hot key or the operations dialog on the issue navigation page one could easily add task to a sprint. If you want to make it really elegant one could by default add to ongoing sprint with the option of adding it to upcomming sprint
{quote}

In case the issue can be a part of many Rapid Boards, there could be a way to select from a list.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-6294].
  {panel}

Once JRA-30144 is completed, code changes are required in order to opt-out if indexing on createIssueLink and removeIssueLink, collect the issues that require re-indexing and perform a bulk re-index on all those issues at the end of the operation.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-6264].
  {panel}

With the same idea as for GHS-6259, we should increment (or decrement) the issues count in the epics cards as soon as the user drop the issue(s) in a epic. We can correct the number after server reply if needed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-6252].
  {panel}

Adding an issue to an epic adds a history entry for the Epic Link value, also the issue change date changes, but the issue isn't reindexed. Using the "Recently Updated" Quick Filter then fails to find the issue

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-6247].
  {panel}

If an invalid epic key is specified in the URL (or is stored in local storage), it is not removed from the state and will continue to be in the URL (and local storage) until a valid epic key is selected.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-6193].
  {panel}
